ENTRY       EC 2.8.2.33                 Enzyme
NAME        N-acetylgalactosamine 4-sulfate 6-O-sulfotransferase;
            GalNAc4S-6ST;
            CHST15 (gene name)
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring sulfur-containing groups;
            Sulfotransferases
SYSNAME     3'-phosphoadenylyl-sulfate:[dermatan]-4-O-sulfo-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine 6-O-sulfotransferase
REACTION    (1) 3'-phospho-5'-adenylyl sulfate + [dermatan]-4-O-sulfo-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine = adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + [dermatan]-4,6-di-O-sulfo-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine [RN:R07288];
            (2) 3'-phospho-5'-adenylyl sulfate + [chondroitin]-4-O-sulfo-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine = adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + [chondroitin]-4,6-di-O-sulfo-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine [RN:R02181]
ALL_REAC    R02181 R07288
SUBSTRATE   3'-phospho-5'-adenylyl sulfate [CPD:C00053];
            [dermatan]-4-O-sulfo-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine;
            [chondroitin]-4-O-sulfo-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine
PRODUCT     adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate [CPD:C00054];
            [dermatan]-4,6-di-O-sulfo-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine;
            [chondroitin]-4,6-di-O-sulfo-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine
COMMENT     The enzyme is activated by divalent cations and reduced glutathione. The enzyme from human transfers sulfate to position 6 of both internal residues and non-reducing terminal GalNAc 4-sulfate residues of chondroitin sulfate and dermatan sulfate. Oligosaccharides derived from chondroitin sulfate also serve as acceptors but chondroitin sulfate E, keratan sulfate and heparan sulfate do not. Differs from EC 2.8.2.17, chondroitin 6-sulfotransferase, in being able to use both chondroitin and dermatan as effective substrates
